BLOCK 7 — Add pei_ruleversion to the EMS Model-Driven App
        + publish the app                                 [BL-121]
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

★ This is the step omitted from the original B01 spec — discovered
  during smoke test, then made permanent via BL-121 (Resolved at
  v58 — template + B01 spec retroactively + B02 spec proactively).
  Without this block, the form generated in Block 6 is NOT
  user-reachable.


─── STEP 7A: Open the EMS Model-Driven App in app designer ──────

WHERE: Power Apps maker → Apps (left rail)
       → find the EMS Model-Driven App
         (the same MDA that hosts pei_rule from B01)
       → "..." menu next to the app name → Edit
       → this opens the modern app designer


─── STEP 7B: Add pei_ruleversion to the app's data ──────────────

In the app designer:

  → Left rail: "Pages" or "Tables" panel (depending on portal
    version — the modern designer calls it "Pages")
  → Click "+ Add page" (or "+ Add table" in older UI)
  → Page type:  Dataverse table
  → Select table:  Rule Version (pei_ruleversion)
  → Show in navigation:  ON (default; verify the toggle is on)
  → Click "Add"

  ★ Suggested navigation placement: under the same nav group as
    Rule from B01 (the L1-B Rule Engine grouping). The Rule
    Version page should appear alongside the Rule page in the
    left nav.

  ★ Optional refinement (NOT required by spec — informational):
    If your app uses nav groups, you can rename the group to
    something like "Rule Engine" to host both Rule and Rule
    Version. Skip if the existing grouping already makes sense.


─── STEP 7C: Verify the page picks up the right form + view ─────

In the app designer, click on the newly added Rule Version page:
  → Right rail shows the page's form binding
  → Form: Information  ← should be selected (the Main form
                          from Block 6)
  → View: All Rule Versions  ← should be selected (the default
                                view from Block 6)

  If either is wrong, change it via the right-rail dropdown.


─── STEP 7D: Save + Publish the app ─────────────────────────────

  → Top-right of the app designer: click Save
  → Then click Publish

  Wait for the publish operation to complete (the toast/banner
  will say "App published successfully" or similar).


